* Ituen, Udofia manhandle Speaker Luke’s press secretary, seize phone In spite of the several police teams mounting roadblocks around the Akwa Ibom State House of Assembly complex and environs preparatory to today’s sitting of lawmakers, the sacked five lawmakers: Idongesit Ituen, Nse Ntuen, Gabriel Tobi, Victor Udofia and Otobong Ndem have taken over the assembly chamber. Led by Mr Idongesit Ituen and Victor Udofia, the five lawmakers moved into the assembly complex moments ago with suspected thugs who sent away Assembly staff, collecting some of their phone gadgets, including that of the press secretary to the Speaker, Mr Kufre Okon. More details to follow…